Canada’s Buyout Activity Recovered in 2010, Globe & Mail Says

-- B y   A l a n   P u r k i s s
-- 
2011-02-18T10:18:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-18/canada-s-buyout-activity-recovered-in-2010-globe-mail-says.html
Private-equity firms put $4.9
billion into 130 Canadian investments last year, up from $4
billion in 2009, the Globe & Mail reported, citing  Thomson
Reuters  and  Canada ’s Venture Capital & Private Equity
Association.  In 2007, the last year before the credit crisis, buyout
firms put $26.4 billion into 185 Canadian transactions, the
newspaper said.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
